cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a new model for complex networks with a degree bound, which has applications in wireless sensor networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
